-- Henkel to pay $5.5 bln for ICI units: Akzo
-- 
-- Mon Aug 6, 2007 4:54am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/08/06/us-akzo-ici-henkel-idUSWLB020220070806

 

 LONDON  (Reuters) - Akzo Nobel ( AKZO.AS ) said on Monday it would sell ICI's ICI.L adhesives and electronic materials units to Germany's Henkel ( HNKG_p.DE ) for 2.7 billion pounds ($5.5 billion) if it succeeds in buying the UK firm. 

 ICI said earlier on Monday that it had opened its books to Akzo after received an improved 8-billion-pound ($16.3 billion) bid proposal from the Dutch group.